## Context

- Forty-fifth run — Covered 8 projects with 8 new journal entries and 4 new tasks.
- Journal #1520 (nf1-loss-pancancer-dependency-atlas):
  - **NF1 pharmacogenomic SL screen (Mol Cancer Ther 2025, PMID 41036607):** >11,000 compounds screened, 27 selective against NF1-deficient Schwann cells. 4 validated in vivo (GEM + xenograft) + synergy with selumetinib. Mirdametinib FDA-approved Feb 2025 for NF1-PN (41% ORR adults). BRD4/PROTAC approach for MPNST. NF1 loss as ESR1-resistance mechanism — KAT6A/B + Menin combos relevant.
- Journal #1521 (swisnf-metabolic-convergence):
  - **Eprenetapopt (APR-246) validates glutathione vulnerability across SWI/SNF-deficient cancers (Sci Rep Dec 2024):** SMARCA4-, SMARCB1-, PBRM1-deficient cells all sensitive. Mechanism: GSH depletion → ROS → apoptosis. Third convergent metabolic axis alongside HMGCR/statins and OXPHOS. FDA-approved for MDS — repurposing feasible.
- Journal #1523 (pancancer-mtap-prmt5-atlas):
  - **IDE892 FPI Mar 9, 2026:** Phase 1 for MTAP-deleted solid tumors (NSCLC, PDAC). ~1,400x selectivity for MTA-PRMT5. Combo with IDE397 (MAT2A) planned mid-2026. CDKN2A pipeline update. Still NO breast cancer enrollment in any PRMT5 trial.
- Journal #1524 (breast-cancer-vulnerability-stratification):
  - **PRMT5 actionable in CDK4/6i-resistant ER+/RB-deficient breast cancer (NatComm 2024):** PRMT5 blocks G1-to-S independent of RB. MTAP-deleted + RB1-lost breast cancers may be double-vulnerable to PRMT5 inhibitors.
- Journal #1525 (rb1-loss-pancancer-dependency-atlas):
  - **INX-315 CDK2i FDA Fast Track for CCNE1-amplified ovarian cancer.** Phase 1 Part A: 10% PR, 63% SD (31 pts). 20% PR in ovarian subset. Study completion Jun 2026.
- Journal #1527 (arid1a-pancancer-sl-atlas):
  - **Tulmimetostat FDA Fast Track for ARID1A-mutant endometrial cancer.** Phase II basket trial (NCT04104776) enrolling dose optimization. ASCO 2026 update submitted.
- Journal #1528 (smarca4-pancancer-sl-atlas):
  - **FHD-909 (LY4050784) SMARCA2 selective inhibitor Phase 1 advancing.** Dose escalation on track since Oct 2024. Lilly collaboration. Separate degrader program also in development.
- Journal #1529 (wrn-msi-pancancer-atlas):
  - **VVD-214/RO7589831 chemistry paper published (J Med Chem 2026, PMID 40964743).** Full SAR disclosure. Phase 1 ongoing mono + pembrolizumab combo in MSI-H tumors.
- Tasks created: research_director #1054 (SWI/SNF eprenetapopt/GSH third axis), #1055 (NF1 SL compounds DepMap cross-reference), #1056 (MTAP+RB1 breast cancer overlap for PRMT5), #1057 (INX-315 CCNE1/RB1 CDK2 convergence).
- Task #151 — vopimetostat per-histology ORR still pending. FDA alignment on 250mg QD dose confirmed. Pivotal PDAC trial ~300 pts planned 2026.
